    </DefBox>

    <CaptionedBlock heading="Other HDB-Approved Breeds We Carry" imagePosition="none">
      <p>The Cavapoo is not your only option for an HDB flat. Alongside it, we regularly place <a href="/puppies/maltipoo" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">Maltipoo puppies</a>, <a href="/puppies/bichonpoo" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">Bichonpoo puppies</a>, <a href="/puppies/mini-dachshund" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">Mini Dachshund puppies</a>, and <a href="/puppies/cockapoo" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">Cockapoo puppies</a>, all approved breeds and crosses that suit flat living.</p>
      <p>Not sure which of them fits your routine? Start with the <a href="/first-time-owners/hdb-breeds" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">HDB-approved dog breeds guide</a>, or take the <a href="/first-time-owners/breed-selector" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">two-minute breed selector</a> and let your actual routine and housing pick the breed.</p>
      <div slot="side" class="clay h-full bg-[var(--color-lilac-900)] p-6 sm:p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-white/60" style="letter-spacing: 0.08em;">Also HDB-approved</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          {[
