  <CaptionedBlock heading="Daily Life with a Cavapoo in Singapore" imageAlt="Cavapoo puppy on a shaded morning walk along a Singapore park connector" imageSrc={parkWalk} imagePosition="left" imageRotate="right">
    <p>A Cavapoo's exercise needs are moderate: 30 to 60 minutes a day, split into a morning and an evening walk around the heat; midday pavement here is genuinely too hot for small paws. Shaded park connectors and void-deck-adjacent green spaces do the job; a Cavapoo doesn't need a landed garden to be happy.</p>
    <p>Rainy weeks and haze days happen, and this is where the breed's size helps: a corridor of indoor fetch, ten minutes of trick training, and a stuffed chew toy will cover an off day without a restless dog by evening.</p>
    <p>Noise-wise, neighbours generally won't have complaints. Cavapoos bark to announce, not to protest all day, provided the alone-time routine is settled early.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

  <PawTrail bg="bg-[var(--color-surface)]" colorClass="text-[var(--color-coral-300)]" />

  <CaptionedBlock heading="Cavapoo Grooming and Coat Care in Our Humid Climate" imageAlt="Cavapoo puppy being brushed with grooming tools from the starter kit" imageSrc={groomingBrush} variant="card">
    <p>Brush 3 to 4 times a week; that wavy, low-shedding coat mats faster in Singapore's humidity than overseas care guides suggest. Book professional grooming every 6 to 8 weeks to keep the coat manageable and nails in check.</p>
    <p>Those soft floppy ears trap moisture here, so make a quick weekly ear check part of the routine; it's the cheapest ear-infection prevention there is. The brush and grooming tools you need for the first months are already in the starter kit.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

  <CloudDivider fillClass="fill-[var(--color-mint-100)]" againstColor="var(--color-surface-card)" />
  <div id="health" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <CaptionedBlock heading="Cavapoo Health: What We Check Before You Take One Home" imageAlt="Cavapoo puppy at a veterinary health check before going home" imageSrc={vetCheck} variant="mid">
      <p>Every Cavapoo goes home vet-checked, vaccinated, dewormed, and microchipped. The Cavapoo health issues worth knowing are three: ear infections from those floppy ears, inherited eye conditions, and patellar luxation, a kneecap issue common to small breeds. We say this once, plainly, because you should hear it from your seller and not from a forum at midnight.</p>
      <p>Feeding is simple: your puppy comes with the small-breed food it's already eating, and the transition to any new brand should be gradual over a week or so. For portioning and feeding-stage guidance, <a href="https://www.royalcanin.com/sg" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">small-breed puppy feeding guidance</a> is a reliable reference, and <a href="/learn/puppy-health" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">our puppy health checks explained</a> covers what we screen and why.</p>
    </CaptionedBlock>
  </div>
