  <div id="first-week" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <CaptionedBlock heading="Your Cavapoo's First Week at Home" imageAlt="Playpen set up and ready before a Cavapoo puppy arrives home for its first week" imageSrc={playpenReady} imagePosition="left">
      <p>Day 0: we deliver, free, at a time that suits you, usually morning or evening. The playpen, bed, water, and toys are set up before your Cavapoo explores the room, and we walk you through all 30+ starter-kit items in person. Learn more about <a href="/delivery" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how our free home delivery and setup works</a>.</p>
      <p>Days 1 to 3: keep it calm. Same food, fixed feeding times, toilet pads where we placed them, and short gentle play. Some night whimpering is normal adjustment, not distress.</p>
      <p>Days 4 to 7: the routine starts to stick. This is the right window to book your free first lesson with an AVS-certified trainer; see <a href="/free-training" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">what the free training lesson covers</a>. And for anything in between, you WhatsApp us; most questions are already answered in the walkthrough, but the ones that aren't get a real reply.</p>
    </CaptionedBlock>
  </div>

